# Cursor scope

## Purpose

Limit Cursor to safe, small edits. Escalate to Claude Code otherwise.

## Allowed (Cursor)

- Documentation cleanup
- File/directory scaffolding
- Typos
- Comments
- Small UI tweaks
- Clear single-file refactor
- Test supplements that do **not** change existing contracts

## Denied (Cursor)

- Service boundary changes
- API / event contract changes
- DB schema or migration changes
- AuthZ / tenant isolation changes
- Temporal Workflow changes
- k3s / Helm / RBAC / NetworkPolicy changes
- AEO scoring changes
- evidence policy changes
- Arbitrary relaxation of `.claude` security settings
- Automatic deployment
- git push
- merge

## Stop and hand off to Claude Code if ANY

- More than 3 files modified
- Impact spans 2+ services
- Changes under `packages/contracts`
- Changes under `packages/schemas`
- Changes under `events`
- Changes under `workflows`
- Changes under `deploy`
- Security or data-isolation impact
- Architecture judgment required

## Bootstrap exception

User-explicit Bootstrap Scaffolding may create initial skeleton files across many paths **once**. After bootstrap, this rule applies fully.

